post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_33345602_33345633_0": {"length": 16, "quality": 0.64, "section_id": 369}}, "n3337": {"so_33345602_33345633_0": {"length": 16, "quality": 0.64, "section_id": 359}}, "n4659": {"so_33345602_33345633_0": {"length": 22, "quality": 0.88, "section_id": 381}}}, "33345602": {"ViewCount": "57", "Body": "<p>I have a code where in I am deriving one class from library class whose default constructor is defined in library. I am not defining any default constructor and as per my understanding C++ compiler should provide it for me but I am getting error </p>\n<pre><code>error: no matching function for call to 'derived::derived()'\ncompilation terminated due to -Wfatal-errors.\n</code></pre>\n<p>My code looks like below code snippet</p>\n<pre><code>#include &lt;iostream&gt;\n\nusing namespace std;\n\nclass base\n{\n    public :\n    base()\n    {\n        ;\n    }\n};\n\nclass derived : public base\n{\n    public :\n    derived(int) : base()\n    {\n        ;\n    }\n};\n\nint main(int argc, char**argv)\n{\n    int i = 0;\n    derived obj;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Can someone please explain me why default constructor is not generated here by compiler ?</p>\n<p>Thanks In advance.</p>\n", "Title": "default constructor for derived class is not provided by compiler", "CreationDate": "2015-10-26T12:18:46.917", "LastActivityDate": "2015-10-26T12:20:27.007", "CommentCount": "1", "PostTypeId": "1", "ClosedDate": "2015-10-26T12:21:02.883", "Id": "33345602", "Score": "0", "OwnerUserId": "5350436", "Tags": "<c++>", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "33345633": {"Id": "33345633", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>Because the default constructor is only generated if you don't add any other non-default constructors.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>If you want, you can even look it up in the C++ standard at \u00a712.1/4</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_33345602_33345633_0\">A <em>default</em> constructor for a class <code>X</code> is a constructor of class <code>X</code>\n  that either has no parameters or else each parameter that is not a\n  function parameter pack has a default argument. <strong>If there is no\n  user-declared constructor for class <code>X</code></strong>, a constructor having no\n  parameters is implicitly declared as defaulted (...).</p>\n</blockquote>\n</hr>", "LastActivityDate": "2015-10-26T12:20:27.007", "CommentCount": "3", "CreationDate": "2015-10-26T12:20:27.007", "ParentId": "33345602", "Score": "0", "OwnerUserId": "3313064"}});